    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`zz` shifts the cursor to the right, as many times as the number of concealed characters before it.\n\nIf you press `zz` in the following line in a vim help text (and the cursor is on e.g. the \"h\" in \"highlights\")\n\n```\nTreesitter uses |nvim_buf_set_extmark()| to set highlights with a default\n```\n\nthe cursor will shift to the right twice.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean runtime/doc/treesitter.txt -c ':496' -c 'normal 50l'\n`zz`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nCursor should not change columns\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n081beb3659\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, VIM - Vi IMproved 9.0 (2022 Jun 28, compiled Aug  3 2024 14:50:46) macOS version - arm64 Included patches: 1-2136, 2142\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacos\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nscreen-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuilt manually",
